		<part id="execution-gap">
			<title>The Execution Gap</title>
			<slide id="vision-strategy-program">
				<title><span title="Why">Vision</span> → <span title="What">Strategy</span> → <span title="How">Program</span> → <span title="Measure">Results</span></title>
				<img title="Grand Canyon" src="grand-canyon.jpg" class="fullsize"/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="digital-transformation-definition">
				<title>Digital Transformation Definition</title>
				<blockquote>
					<p>Digital Transformation <a href="https://hbr.org/2019/07/digital-doesnt-have-to-be-disruptive"><q>means adapting an organization's strategy and structure to capture opportunities enabled by digital technology.</q> <span style="font-size : 75% ;">(Nathan Furr and Andrew Shipilov, <q>Digital Doesn't Have to Be Disruptive</q>, Harvard Business Review 97(4), July/August 2019, pp. 94-103)</span></a></p>
				</blockquote>
			</slide>
			<slide id="leadership-1-2-3">
				<title>Leadership 1-2-3</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Set a <em>vision</em> as the goal to improve the organization</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Digital Transformation</em> will help us to thrive in the increasingly digitalized world</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Define a <em>strategy</em> how to turn the vision into reality</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>APIs</em> are a necessary component of digital transformation</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Have a <em>program</em> to turn the defined strategy into reality</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Designing and building good APIs</em> has business, organizational, and technical aspects</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="boosters">
			<title>Boosters</title>
			<slide id="diversity">
				<title>Landscape Diversity</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em>Why</em> are there certain guidelines for API practices?</li>
					<li><em>What</em> to do can change over time depending on requirements</li>
					<li><em>How</em> to do things can change over time depending on tools and techniques</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-products">
				<title>Product Mindset</title>
				<img src="product-merriam-webster.png" title="Product Definition" style="float: right ; width : 33% ; margin : 0% 4% ; "/>
				<ul>
					<li><em>Business:</em> APIs are conceived as reusable building blocks</li>
					<li><em>Technology:</em> APIs are designed as reusable capabilities</li>
					<li><em>Teams:</em> APIs are managed with a full product lifecycle</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="lighthouse">
				<title>Lighthouse Projects</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Demonstrate <em>real value</em> and not just <em>potential value</em></li>
					<li>Start small and improve and evolve your program and practices</li>
					<li>Move the conversation from <q>saving money</q> to <q>making money</q></li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="blockers">
			<title>Blockers</title>
			<slide id="verticals">
				<title>Verticalized Capabilities</title>
				<ul>
					<li><q>Projects over products</q> means that there is little reuse</li>
					<li>Investments into API tooling and platform could be more effective</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="no-alignment">
				<title>Missing Business Alignment</title>
				<ul>
					<li><q>We have a whole bunch of APIs so we're doing well, right?</q></li>
					<li>APIs may be hard to understand and hard to reuse</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="cutting-cost">
				<title>Saving Money with APIs</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Having a componentized architecture will save money</li>
					<li>Main focus should be on capturing new opportunities</li>
					<li>What does the strategy say about API goals?</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="success-conclusions">
			<title>Conclusions</title>
			<slide id="got-goals">
				<title>Got Goals?</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Have a mission for your API program</li>
					<li>Have goals to check API progress</li>
					<li>Start small but keep an eye on the big picture</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
