	<presentation id="api-lifecycle">
		<title short="API Lifecycle Management">API Lifecycle Management in Practice: Managing APIs as Products</title>
		<toc class="abstract">For an API to directly contribute value to a business, it must be conceived, designed, and managed as a product. With IT becoming increasingly pervasive, we see API products being produced and consumed in more and more places throughout an organization. In this decentralized landscape the question is how to make sure that API products can be produced in a decentralized way, but can still be discovered and used easily. In this session we discuss how the focus of API management increasingly is looking at API consumption as well. We show how to make this work with a model that supports decentralization but at the same time provides a unified catalog of all APIs that makes it easy to discover and use APIs.</toc>
